        &lt;article&gt;&lt;![CDATA[&lt;p&gt;When a major incident is resolved, callers from the parent and related child incidents are notified to validate resolution. Additionally, a communication can be sent to all stakeholders based on the communication plan.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing a major incident does not close all child incidents, and the individual callers need to validate and close their incidents. The only exception is the major incident, or the parent record, which can only be closed by the major incident manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A major incident is not automatically closed based on the incident auto closure property. You can configure the business rule incident autoclose to change the behavior based on any process requirements.&lt;/p&gt;]]&gt;&lt;/article&gt;
